1. Project Overview
Traceback is an AI-powered student learning diagnostics system that analyzes behavioral and performance signals to identify WHY a student is struggling — not just that they are. The system generates a personalized, actionable learning plan for each student based on their specific root cause.

Most educational systems stop at grades. They tell a student they failed, but not why. Traceback goes one level deeper — it traces the failure back to its source, like a programming traceback that finds the exact line where an error originated.

2. Problem Statement
The current educational system has three critical gaps:

•	Grades are reported but not explained. A student with a 40% score who never logged in needs completely different help than a student with a 40% score who studied every day.
•	Professors teaching 200+ students cannot individually diagnose each student's specific struggle.
•	Generic advice ("study more", "attend tutorials") is given to all students regardless of their actual problem.

2.1 The Core Insight
The same symptom — a low score — can have completely different root causes:

Root Cause	What it looks like	What they actually need
No Engagement	Low score + almost no platform activity	Habit building + attendance
Knowledge Gap	Low score + high engagement + multiple attempts	Go back to prerequisites
Declining Performance	Was passing, now failing	Identify what changed
Exam Anxiety	Good coursework, poor formal assessments	Assessment technique training
Needs Support	Consistent but just below threshold	Targeted topic intervention
 
3. System Design
Traceback is built as a three-layer diagnostic pipeline:

3.1 Architecture
Layer 1 — WHAT      (grades, scores, pass/fail)
         ↓
Layer 2 — HOW       (behavioral signals — what we built)
         ↓
Layer 3 — WHY       (answer analysis — v2 roadmap)

Most educational systems only implement Layer 1. Traceback implements Layer 2 fully and has a clear roadmap to Layer 3.

3.2 Two Interfaces
Traceback serves two distinct users with separate interfaces:

Interface	User	Purpose
Student Portal	Individual student	Personal diagnosis, risk scores, learning plan
Professor Dashboard	Instructor / admin	Class-wide analytics, urgency breakdown, pattern detection

3.3 Dataset
The system is built on the OULAD (Open University Learning Analytics Dataset), a real-world dataset from the UK Open University containing anonymized student data.

File	Rows	Key Information
studentInfo.csv	32,593	Demographics, education level, final result
studentAssessment.csv	173,912	Assessment scores and submission dates
assessments.csv	206	Assessment type (TMA/CMA/Exam), weights, dates
studentRegistration.csv	32,593	Registration and dropout dates
studentVle_sample.csv	100,000	Platform interactions (clicks per resource)
vle.csv	6,364	Virtual learning environment activity types
