6. Learning Plan Generator
For each student, the system generates a personalized 4-step learning plan using their actual signal values — not generic templates.

Each plan contains:
•	Diagnosis: plain English explanation of what the data shows, using real numbers
•	Urgency level: CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
•	4 action steps: each with a type, instruction, explanation, and time estimate
•	Encouragement: a personalized closing message

6.1 Example Plan — NO_ENGAGEMENT Student
Student 125535 | Module BBB | Avg Score: 38.2 | Clicks: 3 | Urgency: CRITICAL

Step	Type	Action	Time
1	HABIT	Log in every single day for 7 days	10 min/day
2	CONTENT	Watch all intro videos for module BBB	1-2 hours
3	ASSESSMENT	Submit your next assignment — any score is fine	2-3 hours
4	SUPPORT	Contact your module tutor today	15 min
 
7. System Interfaces
7.1 Professor Dashboard (dashboard.html)
A dark, analytical interface showing class-wide patterns:
•	Root cause distribution (donut chart)
•	Intervention urgency breakdown (bar chart)
•	Average score by root cause
•	Engagement vs final result
•	System KPIs: 28,785 students, 92.5% accuracy, 8,449 need intervention
•	Student search: enter any ID to pull full profile and plan

7.2 Student Portal (student.html)
A warm, personal interface showing only the individual student's data:
•	Login with student ID
•	Personal diagnosis in plain language
•	6 performance signals (score, trend, clicks, late submissions, attempts, std)
•	3 animated risk bars (academic, engagement, persistence)
•	4-step personalized learning plan
•	Encouragement message

The two interfaces are intentionally different in design. The professor view is dark and data-dense. The student view is light, warm, and focused on one person.
 
